           journal="Comput. Vis. Image Underst.",

public class Naturalness
extends AbstractMaskedObject<FImage>
implements ImageAnalyser<MBFImage>, FeatureVectorProvider<DoubleFV>
    Implementation of the Naturalness index (CNI) defined by Huang, Qiao & Wu. The CNI is a single valued summary of how natural the colours in an image are. The index is a value between 0 and 1. Higher values indicate that the colours in the image are more natural .
    Author:
    Jonathon Hare (jsh2@ecs.soton.ac.uk)
